==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia2|hypocoristic}}
'''hypocorism'''
#A form of [[endearment]]; a [[pet]] [[name]]

===Etymology===
Late Latin '''hypocorisma''', a loan from the Greek noun ('''hypokorisma''') that is from the verb ('''hypokorizesthai''' = 'to call by pet names'). The Greek verb ''hypokorizesthai'' is compounded from ([[hypo]]- = 'under') + (korzesthai = 'to [[caress]]'). In the verb you can see the word (koros = '[[boy]]') or (kore = '[[girl]]').

===Meaning===
# a pet name; term of endearment
# the use of pet names

